						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Pillar lying in the well called Basavaṇṇona bhāvi.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1068.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 989, Plavaṅga, Phālguṇa, ba. 3, Sunday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1068 A.D., February 24.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription states that the memorial-stone of Māghaṇandi-Bhaṭṭāraka of Sūrastha-gaṇa was set up by Jākiyabbe of Sindige. Koppaseṭṭi and Chandiseṭṭi were responsible for its erection. </p>						

						</summary>
